LAST-MODIFIED:20260203T212850Z
UID:10053563-1773478800-1773495000@pdxparent.com
SUMMARY:Cedar Hill’s Free Family Fishing Day Event
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy a free family fishing event at Commonwealth Park Lake! Commonwealth Park is located at at 1095 SW Huntington Ave\, Portland\, OR 97225. \nThis is an open fishing opportunity where participants will receive guidance from community mentors in the art of fishing. \nFISHING GEAR PROVIDED WITH REGISTRATION! \n\nRod & Reel\nBait & Tackle\n\nRegistration is required ONLY for participants who need to borrow fishing equipment. Each family member who needs equipment should be registered individually. Participants are also welcome to attend using their own gear without registering. Youth 17 and younger may fish for free. Anyone age 18 or older must have a valid fishing license if they plan to fish. Link to Purchase Fishing License. myodfw.com/fishing/licensing-info \nACTIVITIES INCLUDE:\n\nAngler Education\nShoreline Fishing Experience\nBackyard Bass Casting Practice\nWater Safety\nKnot Tying\nFish Identification Activity\n\nNature Mobile: (Hands-On Science Experience)\n\nView water samples under microscopes\nLearn how water quality is tested\nExplore aquatic life and biodiversity\nDiscover the role of healthy waterways\nEnjoy hands-on\, family-friendly activities\nParticipants are also welcome to attend using their own gear without registering. If you plan to keep any fish please bring a gallon bag\, chest or bucket to transport fish home in.\n\nLink to Register: buff.ly/igzNtfC
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/cedar-hills-free-family-fishing-day-event/
