SUMMARY:Visit Leach Botanical Garden
DESCRIPTION:Explore 16 acres of cultivated and natural gardens in outer Southeast Portland! Families especially love The Aerial Tree Walk (fully ADA accessible) and the gathering meadow with room to relax\, run and explore at this gem of a garden.  \nThe garden is spread across two levels and includes many different types of spaces for gathering\, observing\, learning\, and relaxing. Pathways wind through stands of 80 foot tall Douglas fir trees\, Oregon grape and sword ferns are mixed in with over 2\,000 varieties of plants\, and moss covered stones and branches glow green around every turn. Bring binoculars for the kids; there’s plenty of birds to listen to and see! \nGarden Admission\nMembers: Free\nAdults (19-61): $8\nSeniors (62+): $8\nYouth (6-18): $5\nChildren 5 & Under: Free \nHoliday Closures\nJuly 4th; September 13th\, 2026 for Feast in the Garden; Thanksgiving; Christmas Eve; Christmas Day; New Year Eve; New Year Day
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/visit-leach-botanical-garden/2026-03-14/
LOCATION:Leach Botanical Garden\, 6704 SE 122nd Ave\, Portland\, OR\, Portland\, 97236\, United States
CATEGORIES:Active,Educational,Family Fun,Inclusive,Kids Calendar,Outdoor,Plants & Nature
